
    THE ANC elective conference is going to be a heated affair, but it’s not a match between Orlando Pirates and Kaizer Chiefs.These were the words of Police Minister Fikile Mbalula.The minister was speaking at the launch of the festive season safety campaign at Maponya Mall in Soweto yesterday.Mbalula said he was looking forward to an exciting conference.“Yes, there will be contest, but we must be disciplined. We must respect each other, and we must respect our organisation.”“Hopefully, I will be part of those being elected at the conference. I’m looking forward to serving our people and the ANC, going forward.”Speaking about the safety campaign, Mbalula said cops will be on duty to protect people so that they can enjoy the festive season peacefully.The minister and cops spoke to the shoppers and handed out safety tips pamphlets.Mbalula issued a warning to criminals, saying police would remove them from society and place them in jail.Some shoppers took selfies with the minister.Meanwhile, Transport Minister Joe Maswanganyi launched the road safety campaign on the N1 in Bela Bela, Limpopo, yesterday.He warned road users that bad behaviour wouldn’t be tolerated on the roads.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjssv6Gz3X7THkU2NMsqpTmvPKhMfc3cbYYo1NBMKUFyILWeYBcql6zClCMoTTt9OxRmIHotH0YZTXhjEKvVkXoIYE-8ZxabbZRMpR6qwkvqM_0_5Hb3S7wmp9_UwJkx2p2Qar4Owz_nC1_MopXRmR-Dmo6Ml0AQu4gcHG2RWlL0d8sPxNsf8NAvVqQabLuSGCoOtCQ20NDwfObJGjDhPxF7N-9S2atuQiidQ5c6r7Xs_pbz06DeqBxaKOQwuM0r9WFaLUvxEjXWB5wABxatwyyMokzVKWNs\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzHpsktGgLiTmEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
